key_quotes: I don't understand the differences between a pipeline when you're in the candidate record versus the pipeline as a standalone.

If I'm in a pipeline within a candidate record and I move a candidate to out of process, then a window pops up and I can choose why and I can put notes in it, right? But if I do it from the pipeline itself, that's no option.
So the difference is how you have it set for the drag and drop action.
If you were to change your step in your pipeline setup to pop up then you would see that same screen.

qa_pairs.question: What is the difference between a pipeline in the candidate record and the pipeline as a standalone?
qa_pairs.answer: The difference is how you have it set for the drag and drop action. When you're in the candidate record, you're forced to pop up a window to add notes, but in the standalone pipeline, it automatically moves without the option to add notes.

qa_pairs.question: How can I change the pipeline setup to allow adding notes when moving candidates?
qa_pairs.answer: You can go to system, pipeline setup, and for every active and out of process step, change the drag and drop action to pop up instead of just moving it. This will allow you to add more detail.
